{"title_page": "Tiger & Bunny", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Tiger & Bunny\n| image           = Tiger & Bunny vol 1.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first Blu-ray volume featuring Kotetsu Kaburagi (left) and Barnaby Brooks (right).\n| ja_kanji        = \u30bf\u30a4\u30ac\u30fc\uff06\u30d0\u30cb\u30fc\n| ja_romaji       = Taig\u0101 Ando Ban\u012b\n| genre           = [[Adventure genre|Adventure]], [[comedy]],<ref>{{cite web|title=The Official Website for TIGER & BUNNY|url=https://www.viz.com/tiger-bunny|publisher=Viz Media|accessdate=May 30, 2018}}</ref> [[superhero fiction|superhero]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Loo |first1=Egan |title=Tiger & Bunny Superhero Anime's 1st Film Teaser Streamed (Updated) |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-04-06/tiger-and-bunny-superhero-anime-1st-film-teaser-streamed |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=December 30, 2018 |date=April 6, 2012}}</ref><!-- Genres should be based on what reliable sources list them as and not on personal interpretations. Limit of the three most relevant genres in accordance with [[MOS:A&M]]. -->\n| creator = [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = [[Keiichi Sato]]<br/>Kunihiro Mori <small>(Chief, #14-25)</small>\n| producer        = Hiroo Maruyama<br/>Chinatsu Matsui<br/>Kazuhiko Tamura\n| writer          = Masafumi Nishida\n| music           = [[Yoshihiro Ike]]\n| studio          = Sunrise\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n  | AUS = [[Siren Visual]]\n  | NA  = [[Viz Media]]\n  | UK  = [[Kaz\u00e9|Kaz\u00e9 UK]]\n}}\n| network         = [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]], [[Mainichi Broadcasting System|MBS]], [[Tokyo MX]]\n| network_en      = {{English anime network\n | NA = [[Neon Alley]]\n}}\n| first           = April 3, 2011\n| last            = September 18, 2011\n| episodes        = 25\n| episode_list    = List of Tiger & Bunny episodes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]]\n| illustrator     = Sakakibara Mizuki\n| publisher       = [[Kadokawa Shoten]]\n| publisher_en    = [[Viz Media]]\n| magazine        = Newtype Ace\n| demographic     = [[Seinen manga|''Seinen'']]\n| first           = October 2, 2011\n| last            = November 2014\n| volumes         = 9\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Tiger & Bunny On Air Jack!\n| developer       = [[Namco Bandai Games]]\n| publisher       = [[Namco Bandai Games]]\n| genre           = [[Visual novel]]\n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Portable]]\n| released        = September 20, 2012\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = film\n| title           = Tiger & Bunny: The Beginning\n| director        = [[Yoshitomo Yonetani]]\n| producer        = \n| writer          = Masafumi Nishida\n| music           = [[Yoshihiro Ike]]\n| studio          = [[Sunrise (studio)|Sunrise]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n  | AUS = Siren Visual\n  | NA  = Viz Media\n  | UK  = [[Anime Limited]]\n}}\n| released        = September 22, 2012\n| runtime         = 90 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Tiger & Bunny Heroes Day\n| developer       = [[D3 Publisher]]\n| publisher       = [[D3 Publisher]]\n| genre           = [[Visual novel]]\n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Portable]]\n| released        = March 20, 2013\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = film\n| title           = Tiger & Bunny: The Rising\n| director        = [[Yoshitomo Yonetani]]\n| producer        = \n| writer          = Masafumi Nishida\n| music           = [[Yoshihiro Ike]]\n| studio          = [[Sunrise (studio)|Sunrise]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n  | AUS = Siren Visual\n  | NA  = Viz Media\n  | UK  = Anime Limited\n}}\n| released        = February 8, 2014\n| runtime         = 90 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Tiger & Bunny'''''|\u30bf\u30a4\u30ac\u30fc\uff06\u30d0\u30cb\u30fc|Taig\u0101 Ando Ban\u012b|}} is a 2011 Japanese [[anime]] television series produced by [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]] under the direction of [[Keiichi Satou]]. The screenplay was written by Masafumi Nishida, with original character design by [[Masakazu Katsura]]. The series began its broadcast run in Japan on April 3, 2011 on [[Tokyo MX]], followed by rebroadcasts on [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]] and [[Mainichi Broadcasting System|MBS]], and ended on September 17, 2011.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-11-23/sunrise-to-launch-tiger-and-bunny-tv-series-next-april | title = News: Sunrise to Start Tiger & Bunny Hero TV Series in April | publisher = Anime News Network | date = November 23, 2010 | accessdate = February 23, 2011}}</ref> [[Viz Media]] simulcast the series on [[Hulu]] and [[Anime News Network]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.viz.com/content/life-isn%E2%80%99t-easy-when-you%E2%80%99re-fulltime-superhero-hot-new-anime-action-series-tiger-bunny-simul|title=Life Isn't Easy When You're a Fulltime Superhero in Hot New Anime Action Series ''Tiger &amp; Bunny'', Simulcasting on VizAnime.com|work=Viz.com|publisher=Viz Media|date=March 24, 2011|accessdate=March 28, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110527155940/http://www.viz.com/content/life-isn%E2%80%99t-easy-when-you%E2%80%99re-fulltime-superhero-hot-new-anime-action-series-tiger-bunny-simul|archivedate=May 27, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> It is set in a futuristic city where heroes fight crime whilst promoting real life sponsors, focusing on two superheroes, the old-fashioned Kotetsu T. \"Wild Tiger\" Kaburagi and the rookie hero Barnaby \"Bunny\" Brooks Jr., as they are forced by their employers to work together.\n\nA one-shot [[manga]] drawn by [[Masakazu Katsura]] was published in [[Shueisha]]'s ''[[Weekly Young Jump]]'' magazine on August 4, 2011<ref name=\"animenewsnetwork1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-07-13/zetman-katsura-draws-tiger-and-bunny-1-shot-manga |title=Zetman's Katsura Draws Tiger & Bunny 1-Shot Manga |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2011-07-13 |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref> and the production of two films based on the series were announced during a special event on November, 2011. The first film, entitled ''Tiger & Bunny: The Beginning'' was released on September 22, 2012. The second film, ''Tiger & Bunny: The Rising'', was released on February 8, 2014.<ref name=\"movie2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-09-22/tiger-and-bunny-2nd-film-titled-slated-for-next-fall |title=Tiger & Bunny's 2nd Film Titled, Slated for Next Fall |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2012-09-22 |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref>\n\nA second season was announced in March 2020. It is scheduled for a release sometime in 2022.\n\n== Plot ==\n{{see|List of Tiger & Bunny characters}}\nThe series takes place in \"NC 1978\" in a fictional, re-imagined version of New York City called Stern Bild City, where 45 years before, superpowered individuals known as \"NEXT\" (an acronym standing for '''N'''oted '''E'''ntities with e'''X'''traordinary '''T'''alents) started appearing and some of them became superheroes. Each of the city's most famous superheroes work for a sponsor company and their uniforms also contain advertising for real-life companies. Their heroic activity is broadcast on the popular television show \"Hero TV\", where they accumulate points for each heroic feat accomplished (arresting criminals or saving civilians, for example) and the best ranked hero of the season is crowned \"King of Heroes\".\n\nThe story mainly focuses on veteran hero Kotetsu T. Kaburagi, a.k.a. ''Wild Tiger'', who is assigned a new partner: a young man named Barnaby Brooks, Jr. However, Barnaby and Kotetsu have trouble working together, as they have conflicting opinions on how a superhero should act, while at the same time they are trying to crack the mystery of the murder of Barnaby's parents. In addition, the appearance of a homicidal vigilante NEXT named \"Lunatic\" stirs up the public and makes them question the place of heroes in the city.\n\n==Media==\n\n===Anime===\n{{main|List of Tiger & Bunny episodes}}\nThe anime by [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]] aired in Japan between April 3, 2011 and September 17, 2011. It was also simulcast with English subtitles on various streaming sites such as [[Hulu]], [[Viz Media]] and [[Anime News Network]]. The anime has been licensed by [[Viz Media]] in North America and [[Kaz\u00e9]] distributed through [[Manga Entertainment]] in the United Kingdom. For the first thirteen episodes, the opening theme is {{nihongo|\"Orion wo Nazoru\"|\u30aa\u30ea\u30aa\u30f3\u3092\u306a\u305e\u308b||\"Trace of Orion\"}} by Unison Square Garden while the ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Hoshi no Sumika\"|\u661f\u306e\u3059\u307f\u304b||\"A Star's Dwelling\"}} by Aobouzu. For episodes fourteen onwards, the opening theme is \"Missing Link\" by Novels while the ending theme is \"Mind Game\" by Tamaki.\n\nThe series began broadcasting in the United States and Canada on [[Viz Media]]'s online network, [[Neon Alley]], on October 2, 2012. On October 15, 2017, the series began running on [[Netflix]].<ref>https://www.netflix.com/title/80039972</ref>\n\nA second anime series was announced on January 4, 2018.<ref name=\"series2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-01-04/tiger-and-bunny-gets-new-anime-series-project/.126082 |title=Tiger & Bunny Gets New Anime Series Project |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2018-01-04 |accessdate=2018-01-05}}</ref> It is titled ''[[Double Decker! Doug & Kirill]]'', and it premiered on September 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-03-16/new-tiger-and-bunny-anime-project-revealed-as-double-decker-doug-and-kirill-original-anime-series/.129081|title=New Tiger & Bunny Anime Project Revealed as Double Decker! Doug & Kirill Original Anime Series|work=Anime News Network|access-date=2018-03-16|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn March 30, 2019, [[Nikkan Sports]] announced that a sequel to the original ''Tiger & Bunny'' series is currently in production.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/201903300000345.html|title=\u897f\u7530\u5f81\u53f2\u6c0f\u300c\u30bf\u30a4\u30d0\u30cb\u300d\u7d9a\u7de8\u306e\u811a\u672c\u62c5\u5f53\u3068\u660e\u304b\u3059 - \u82b8\u80fd : \u65e5\u520a\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4|website=nikkansports.com|language=ja|access-date=2019-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animeherald.com/2019/03/30/tiger-masafumi-nishida-writing-the-story/|title=Tiger & Bunny Gets Second Anime Series; Masafumi Nishida Writing the Story|date=2019-03-30|website=Anime Herald|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-30}}</ref> On April 2, 2020, the sequel was announced as Tiger & Bunny 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/tiger-and-bunny-season-2-release-date-2022-tiger-bunny-2-sequel-new-studio-bn-pictures/ |title=Tiger And Bunny Season 2 release date confirmed for 2022: Tiger & Bunny 2 has a new studio BN Pictures |publisher=[[Monsters and Critics]] |date= April 2, 2020 |accessdate= April 2, 2020}}</ref> Voice actors Hiroaki Hirata and Masakazu Morita are returning to voice their respective characters. The anime is being produced by studio BN Pictures, with director Mitsuko Kase replacing director Keiichi Satou. The character designs will be created by manga artist Masakazu Katsura.\n\n====Films====\nThe production of two films based on the series was announced during a special event on November 13, 2011. The first film, titled ''Tiger & Bunny: The Beginning'' was released in Japan on September 22, 2012, also receiving screenings in the United States, the United Kingdom and other countries, and was released on Blu-ray-Disc and DVD on February 22, 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=//www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-09-05/1st-tiger-and-bunny-film-to-hold-n-american-premiere-in-san-francisco|title=1st Tiger & Bunny Film to Hold N. American Premiere in San Franciscoposted on 2012-09-05 15:40 EDT|work=Anime News Network|date=September 5, 2012|accessdate=June 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=//www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-07-30/tiger-and-bunny/the-beginning-london-cinema-screening-on-september-23|title=Tiger & Bunny: The Beginning London Cinema Screening on September 23|work=Anime News Network|date=July 30, 2012<!-- from url -->|accessdate=June 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=//www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-11-16/1st-tiger-and-bunny-film-bd/dvd-to-have-english-subs|title=1st Tiger & Bunny Film's BD/DVD to Have English Subsposted on 2012-11-16 16:20 EST|work=Anime News Network|date=November 16, 2012|accessdate=June 18, 2014}}</ref> The first half of the film recaps the first few episodes whilst also introducing a new story. A second film, ''Tiger & Bunny: The Rising'', is an entirely new work which was released on February 8, 2014.<ref name=\"Anime News Network\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2013-04-26/2nd-tiger-and-bunny-film-kotetsu-design-2014-delay-revealed |title=2nd Tiger & Bunny Film's Kotetsu Design, 2014 Delay Revealed |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2013-04-26 |accessdate=2013-04-26}}</ref> The second movie also takes place about a year after the anime finale, so sometime around the epilogue, with Kotetsu's identity now public, and Tiger & Bunny return to their team dynamic.\n\n===Manga===\nA one-shot [[manga]] drawn by [[Masakazu Katsura]] was released in [[Shueisha]]'s ''[[Weekly Young Jump]]'' magazine on August 4, 2011,<ref name=\"animenewsnetwork1\"/> followed by a serialized manga series drawn by Hiroshi Ueda which began serialization in ''Miracle Jump'' magazine on October 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2011-07-26/tiger-and-bunny-gets-manga-series |title=Tiger & Bunny Gets Manga Series |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2011-07-26 |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref> The manga, along with a [[Yonkoma|4-Panel]] Comic Anthology by various artists, has been licensed in North America by Viz Media and was released in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-10-14/viz-adds-tiger-and-bunny-manga-taiyo-matsumoto-sunny |title=Viz Adds Tiger & Bunny Manga, Taiyo Matsumoto's Sunny |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2012-10-14 |accessdate=2012-10-15}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA video game titled {{nihongo|''Tiger & Bunny On Air Jack!''|TIGER&BUNNY \u30aa\u30f3\u30a8\u30a2\u30b8\u30e3\u30c3\u30af\uff01|Taig\u0101 Ando Ban\u012b On Ea Jyakku!}} was developed by [[Namco Bandai Games]] for the [[PlayStation Portable]] for release on September 20, 2012. The game was announced by Sunrise producer Masayuki Ozaki on July 31, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2011-07-31/producer/namco-bandai-makes-tiger-and-bunny-anime-game |title=Producer: Namco Bandai Makes Game of Tiger & Bunny Anime |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2011-07-31 |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2012-04-10/tiger-and-bunny-on-air-jack-game-headed-to-psp-this-fall |title=Tiger & Bunny On Air Jack! Game Headed to PSP This Fall |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2012-04-10 |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref> A second game, {{nihongo|''Tiger & Bunny Heroes Day''|TIGER&BUNNY\uff5e\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed\u30fc\u30ba \u30c7\u30a4\uff5e|Taig\u0101 Ando Ban\u012b ~H\u012br\u014dzu Dei~}}, was released by [[D3 Publisher]] for the PlayStation Portable in March 20, 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|author=Hodgkins, Crystalyn|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2012-12-12/tiger-and-bunny-heroes-day-psp-game-revealed|title=Tiger & Bunny Heroes Day PSP Game Revealed|work=Anime News Network|date=2012-12-12|accessdate=2014-01-26}}</ref>\n\n===Stage play===\nA stage play titled ''Tiger & Bunny the Live'' ran at Tokyo's Zepp Diver City theater from August 24 to September 1, 2012 featuring the voice actors for main characters Kotetsu T. Kaburagi and Barnaby Brooks Jr. reprising their roles. It also featured two new characters, Brian Vai and Babel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2012-04-30/tiger-and-bunny-lead-actors-reprise-roles-for-stage-play |title=Tiger & Bunny's Lead Actors Reprise Roles for Stage Play |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2012-04-30 |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref>\n\n===Live-action film===\nOn October 9, 2015, [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]] announced at their [[New York Comic Con]] panel that a live-action [[Hollywood]] film adaptation of ''Tiger & Bunny'' is in the works.<ref name=\"live-action Tiger and Bunny\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-10-09/imagine-entertainment-to-produce-live-action-tiger-and-bunny-film/.94016|title=Imagine Entertainment to Produce Live-Action Tiger & Bunny Film|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2015-10-09}}</ref> The film will be produced by [[Ron Howard]] and [[Brian Grazer]] through their production company [[Imagine Entertainment]] and [[Global Road Entertainment]], along with series producer Masayuki Ozaki from [[Bandai Namco Pictures]] and [[Sandy Climan|Sanford Climan]] and [[Annmarie Bailey]] through All Nippon Entertainment Works. Imagine's Erica Huggins will oversee the project.\n\n==Marketing==\n\n===In-show advertising===\nEach of the heroes in the series is sponsored by fictional and non fictional companies. These include large brands such as [[Pepsi]] and [[Bandai]], others are [[Amazon.com|Amazon.com.jp]], [[SoftBank]], [[UStream]] and [[Domino's Pizza]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tigerandbunny.net/placement/index.html#p02 |title=PLACEMENT &#124; \u5287\u5834\u7248 TIGER & BUNNY -The Beginning |publisher=TigerandBunny.net |date= |accessdate=2016-02-17 }}</ref> The company logos are not visible in the manga adaptation nor the episodes on Netflix.\n\n===Toys===\nIn September 2011, [[Bandai|Bandai's]] Tamashii Nations division released a series of figures under their S.H. Figuarts line. The first of these was a Wild Tiger action figure.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anime-island.com/products/tiger-bunny-wild-tiger-s-h-figuarts-action-figure.html |title=Tiger & Bunny Wild Tiger S.H. Figuarts Action Figure |publisher=Anime-island.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-26}}</ref> The figure was a success, with most Japanese retailers/dealers being caught off guard and the figure selling out quickly.{{cn|date=April 2019}} The next to be released was a Barnaby Brooks Jr. (a.k.a. Bunny) action figure, followed by figures of Rock Bison and Sky High. All of the figures feature diecast metal parts and sponsor logos printed on the armor, such as [[Softbank]] & [[Amazon (company)|Amazon.jp]].<ref>http://www.anime-island.com/product_images/v/995/4543112694690b__61784_zoom.jpg</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nIn [[Anime News Network]]'s Spring 2011 preview guide, Zac Bertschy gave the first episode a 5 out of 5. He states that it set up a great and clever superhero premise with some twists. He also said that the show has \"the potential to be the kind of smash hit we haven't seen in a long time\".<ref>{{cite web  |first = Zac | last = Bertschy | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2011-04-02/zac|title = Zac Bertschy - Spring 2011 Anime Preview Guide | publisher = [[Anime News Network]] | date = 2011-04-02 | accessdate = 2011-04-03}}</ref> While Theron Martin gave it a 4.5 out of 5, he credits Sunrise for their excellent hero designs and CGI animation. He also stated that it had the look and feel of an American animated series.<ref>{{cite web| first = Theron | last = Martin | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2011-04-02/theron | title = Theron Martin - Spring 2011 Anime Preview Guide | publisher = Anime News Network | date = 2011-02-04 | accessdate = 2011-04-03}}</ref>\n\n''Tiger & Bunny: The Rising'' grossed \u00a5130 million in its opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/eternal-zero-tops-japan-bo-for-8th-week|title= Eternal Zero tops Japan B.O. for 8th week|author= Kevin Ma|date= February 13, 2014|accessdate= February 13, 2014|work= [[Film Business Asia]]|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140221122347/http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/eternal-zero-tops-japan-bo-for-8th-week|archivedate= February 21, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn a 2019 ''[[Forbes]]''{{'s}} article about the best anime of the 2010s decade, Lauren Orsini considered it to be one of the five best anime of 2011; she wrote, \"This love letter to the superhero genre is a refreshing break from the decade's grittier superhero franchise, ''[[Avengers (comics)|The Avengers]]''\".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/laurenorsini/2019/12/02/the-best-anime-of-the-decade2010-and-2011/#1321fdd423f8 | title=The Best Anime Of The Decade - 2010 And 2011 | first=Lauren | last=Orsini | date=December 2, 2019 | work=Forbes | accessdate=December 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.tigerandbunny.net/}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120906002738/http://tb-thelive.net/index.html Official stage play website]\n* [http://www.bandaigames.channel.or.jp/list/tiger_bunny/ Official Tiger & Bunny on Air Jack! website]\n* {{Official website|http://www.mbs.jp/tigerandbunny/|MBS official website}}\n* [http://www.hulu.com/tiger-and-bunny/ Hulu's Streaming Site]\n* {{ann|anime|12198}}\n* {{ann|film|13781|Tiger & Bunny \u2013 The Beginning}}\n* {{ann|film|14819|Tiger & Bunny \u2013 The Rising}}\n\n{{Sunrise}}\n{{Bandai Namco Pictures}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tiger and Bunny}}\n[[Category:2011 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2011 manga]]\n[[Category:2012 anime films]]\n[[Category:2012 video games]]\n[[Category:2014 anime films]]\n[[Category:Adventure anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Animated films based on animated series]]\n[[Category:Animated superhero television series]]\n[[C